
[1]benight

   BENI'GHT, v.t. [be and night.] To involve in darkness; to shroud with
   the shades of night.

   The clouds benight the sky.

   1. To overtake with night; as a benighted traveler.

   2. To involve in moral darkness, or ignorance; to debar from
   intellectual light; as benighted nations, or heathen.
